reviews.text: Stopped by after grabbing some parts for my daughter's car from the Mt. Airy pick your part. Wasn't expecting much but always wanted to try the pizza. Grabbed 2 slices of mushroom and onion. The pizza is delicious. Definitely NY style thin but they make the bottom crispy....that was an AWESOME difference. Can't wait to come back again.

J&P‚Äôs is a Mt. Airy treasure! A welcoming family atmosphere with an extensive menu of delicious food! Antonio, our server, was very friendly and provided great service to our larger party. Lindsey, the manager, greeted us with a warm smile when we entered the restaurant! Our family has enjoyed many meals for over 25 years and highly recommend this tradition to other families!

Wish I browsed the menu longer, it was cold and windy today and some Italian wedding soup would of been killer today but I was hungry and in a hurry.

I got 2 slices of pizza for lunch, very little grease in the box which was good. Slices weren't overcooked on the bottom, definitely new york style. Thin but not paper thin, good topping to dough ratio.

Looked like a large indoor eating area with a big bar.

Interested to try anything on the menu really, has take out style food but also full Italian dinners.

First I have to say that I rarely write a review, good or bad but this has to be said. J and P isn‚Äôt just where you meet up with family or friends, it‚Äôs where you make friends and family. My husband and I have been going to J and P since we moved here over 2 years ago and have met such wonderful people, from customers to the wonderful staff who are amazing!
Recently my grandson had his Confirmation. We decided to have the party at J and P. I talked with Lindsey and we set it in motion. Lindsey made everything so easy. The party was a hit! My family being 100% Italian I was a little worried lol. They loved the food! Our server Kelly was amazing!
Thank you J and P for a great time.
We moved down here from NY/NJ area 20 years ago and this is the best NYC/Jersey-style pizza we‚Äôve found.  It‚Äôs very good!

detailedReviews.author: Bryan Walsh
detailedReviews.text:
If you have allergies, don't bother coming here or be duped by their dairy-free and gluten-free options. They put whatever they want on your pizza no matter what you order.

Our family of eight has three children with significant dairy allergies and because of this, we ordered three pizzas, two of them dairy-free.

All three pizzas, however, were made with regular dairy cheese, which we didn't realize until all three of the children with allergies started having allergic reactions in the restaurant. We had to take the youngest out of the restaurant immediately because she started swelling up and choking.

That was at 8:30pm. It is now 1am and the youngest is still up crying, itching with hives, and continues to cough and choke.  All because someone in the kitchen couldn't be bothered to read the order, pay attention to what they were making, or care enough about customers.

To top it all off, my son pointed out a curly black hair my salad bowl and sorry, no one in my family has black hair.

They didn't end up charging us for the meal, but that doesn't do much when you have to listen to your three year old daughter unnecessarily suffer and debate whether to take her to the hospital or not. Don't offer a dairy free option if doesn't matter to you whether or not you use it.

This was an embarrassment. Clearly won't be coming back.

detailedReviews.author: Julie
detailedReviews.text: Super disappointed in this place. I specifically ordered gluten- and dairy-free pizza for my kids who have severe allergies. Instead, we were served regular cheese pizza‚Äîwhich led to serious allergic reactions. This is completely unacceptable and dangerous. If a restaurant offers allergy-friendly options, their staff absolutely must be trained to handle those requests properly. Clearly, that wasn't the case here. To make matters worse, while trying to get to the bottom of whether or not they used regular cheese, I found a hair in another dish we ordered. Between the careless handling of allergy orders and poor hygiene, this experience was beyond frustrating. I hope they take this seriously before someone ends up in the hospital.

detailedReviews.author: Jeffrey Raymonds
detailedReviews.text:
J & P is a local treasure. I always start with a bowl of cream of crab and their boneless garlic wings. Slowly, I peel the crisped-to-perfection breading off of my delectable chicken nibbles. I save this newly formed pile of breaded gold for later. NOW that the chicken nugget is reverted to its natural state, I slowly soak these naked nuggets in an extra dirty martini (grey goose, no vermouth, extra olives). After the crisp nip of olives has soaked into my tendies, a light brush into my cream of crab. It's like the scene in ratatouille (the rat movie). The main character (Remy rat) puts to unlike flavor combinations in his rat mouth to make something extraordinaryl! Words can't describe the symphony of flavor, but I'll try nonetheless: (IMAGINE)dectant deep fried naked chicken, with the slightest earthy olive tang, balanced transformitively with a combination of crustacean cream, finished with a hint of the driest sherry. Truly a Masterpiece you must try.

To finish my meal, I take the chunky tang of their homemade blue cheese dressing (came with my wings) to fill the olives left in my martini. Truly an Italian delicacy. Don't forget the best part! I roll those stuffed puppies, encrusting them perfectly in crisp garlic I removed carefully from my chicken. A bliss of texture and sharpness delight my senses.

I can not recommend this restaurant enough. The menu is massive. ENDLESS COMBIATIONS OF AUTHENTIC ITALIAN CHARM AWAIT!

the staff are also lovely.

I called to report the behavior the next day. It must improve for me to go back again.
